com.siperian.sif.message.hm

Class EntityGraphFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.hm.OneHopFilter
      • com.siperian.sif.message.hm.EntityGraphFilter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class EntityGraphFilter
extends OneHopFilter
    This is the filter criteria for GetEntityGraphRequest. It extends the capabilities of OneHopFilter. In additions to the options in OneHopFilter, this filter can be used to limit the size of the graph returned based on the depth (number of hops), breadth (number of relationships at each hop) and total number of Relationships.

    See Also:
    GetOneHopRequest, GetEntityGraphRequest, OneHopFilter, Serialized Form

      • setMaximumBreadth

        public void setMaximumBreadth(int maximumBreadth)
        Set the maximum number of Relationships that an Entity can have before it is traversed. Default is 10.

        For example if an Entity has 100 Relationships, and "maximumBreadth" is 10, Relationships for that Entity will not be returned in the GetEntityGraphResponse. The EntityInfo object corresponding to that Entity in the GetEntityGraphResponse will have the appropriate information so the caller can determine why Relationships for the Entity were not returned. In our example, EntityInfo.getRelationshipCount() will return 100, EntityInfo.isTraversed() will return false and EntityInfo.isListNode() will return true.

        Parameters:
        maximumBreadth - Maximum number of relationships for a single Entity.

      • setMaximumRelationships

        public void setMaximumRelationships(int maximumRelationships)
        Set the maximum number of total Relationships that should be returned. Default is 100.

        For example if maximumRelationships is 100, maximumDepth is 10 and after six (6) hops less than 100 Relationships have been fetched. Since the number of Relationships after 6th hop is less than 100, the Hub Server fetches Relationships for the leaf Entities (7th hop). If after the 7th hop more than 100 (say 105) Relationships have been fetched, Hub Server does not try to fetch Relationships for the 8th, 9th or 10th hops. The Relationships already fetched (105 in our example) are returned in the GetEntityGraphResponse.

        The EntityInfo objects corresponding to the leaf Entities from the 7th hop will return false for both EntityInfo.isTraversed() and EntityInfo.isListNode().

        Parameters:
        maximumRelationships - Maximum number of total Relationships that should be returned.

        public void setCountLeafRelations(boolean countLeafRelations)
        Sets/resets flag indicating if hub should provide count relations at entities being last hop node in resulting graph. If set to false, hub will return 0 as relationshipCount and traversed = false for those nodes.
        Parameters:
